\"show_title\":\"\",\"link_titles\":\"\",\"show_tags\":\"\",\"show_intro\":\"\",\"info_block_position\":\"\",\"show_category\":\"\",\"link_category\":\"\",\"show_parent_category\":\"\",\"link_parent_category\":\"\",\"show_author\":\"\",\"link_author\":\"\",\"show_create_date\":\"\",\"show_modify_date\":\"\",\"show_publish_date\":\"\",\"show_item_navigation\":\"\",\"show_icons\":\"\",\"show_print_icon\":\"\",\"show_email_icon\":\"\",\"show_vote\":\"\",\"show_hits\":\"\",\"show_noauth\":\"\",\"urls_position\":\"\",\"alternative_readmore\":\"\",\"article_layout\":\"\",\"show_publishing_options\":\"\",\"show_article_options\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_backend\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_frontend\":\"\"}',1,24,'','',1,12,'{\"robots\":\"\",\"author\":\"\",\"rights\":\"\",\"xreference\":\"\"}',0,'*',''),(28,64,'Interview tips','interview-tips','<div class=\"itemHeader\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; color: #666666; font-family: sans-serif; line-height: 18px;\">\r\n<h1 class=\"itemTitle\" style=\"margin: 0.9em 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 20px; line-height: 1.1; font-family: Oswald, Helvetica, Verdana, Aria, sans-serif; font-weight: normal; color: #333333;\">Job Interview Success Tips</h1>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"itemBody\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; color: #666666; font-family: sans-serif; line-height: 18px;\">\r\n<div class=\"itemFullText\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px;\">\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.7em 0px 1.5em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; line-height: 1.5;\">Follow these job interview tips to set yourself apart and increase your chances of being hired.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"margin: 1.125em 0px 0.6em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.125; font-family: Oswald, Helvetica, Verdana, Arial, sans-serif; color: #00457c;\">I.     Preparation</h2>\r\n<ul style=\"margin: 0.7em 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; list-style: none; line-height: 1.5;\">\r\n<li style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 10px; border: 0px; background-image: url(\'http://www.project1.com/templates/technik/images/bullet.png\'); background-attachment: scroll; background-color: transparent; line-height: 1.5; overflow: visible; background-position: 0px 7px; background-repeat: no-repeat no-repeat;\">Learn about the client and visit their website. Know about their industry, products &amp; services, IT environment, company culture, current news items.</li>\r\n<li style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 10px; border: 0px; background-image: url(\'http://www.project1.com/templates/technik/images/bullet.png\'); background-attachment: scroll; background-color: transparent; line-height: 1.5; overflow: visible; background-position: 0px 7px; background-repeat: no-repeat no-repeat;\">Understand the job requirements including description of the role, technical skills, application skills</li>\r\n<li style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 10px; border: 0px; background-image: url(\'http://www.project1.com/templates/technik/images/bullet.png\'); background-attachment: scroll; background-color: transparent; line-height: 1.5; overflow: visible; background-position: 0px 7px; background-repeat: no-repeat no-repeat;\">Know the details on your resume. Be comfortable and articulate in describing your experience. Make sure you are able to answer any questions that pertain to what’s written on your resume.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2 style=\"margin: 1.125em 0px 0.6em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.125; font-family: Oswald, Helvetica, Verdana, Arial, sans-serif; color: #00457c;\">II.    Phone Interview</h2>\r\n<ul style=\"margin: 0.7em 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; list-style: none; line-height: 1.5;\">\r\n<li style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 10px; border: 0px; background-image: url(\'http://www.project1.com/templates/technik/images/bullet.png\'); background-attachment: scroll; background-color: transparent; line-height: 1.5; overflow: visible; background-position: 0px 7px; background-repeat: no-repeat no-repeat;\">Prepare and treat the phone screen as you would an in-person interview.</li>\r\n<li style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 10px; border: 0px; background-image: url(\'http://www.project1.com/templates/technik/images/bullet.png\'); background-attachment: scroll; background-color: transparent; line-height: 1.5; overflow: visible; background-position: 0px 7px; background-repeat: no-repeat no-repeat;\">Use a landline phone or strong cell signal if possible to maximize clarity.</li>\r\n<li style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 10px; border: 0px; background-image: url(\'http://www.project1.com/templates/technik/images/bullet.png\'); background-attachment: scroll; background-color: transparent; line-height: 1.5; overflow: visible; background-position: 0px 7px; background-repeat: no-repeat no-repeat;\">Make sure you are in quiet surroundings where you can speak comfortably without distractions.</li>\r\n<li style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 10px; border: 0px; background-image: url(\'http://www.project1.com/templates/technik/images/bullet.png\'); background-attachment: scroll; background-color: transparent; line-height: 1.5; overflow: visible; background-position: 0px 7px; background-repeat: no-repeat no-repeat;\">Have your resume in front of you along with a pen &amp; paper so you can take notes.</li>\r\n<li style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 10px; border: 0px; background-image: url(\'http://www.project1.com/templates/technik/images/bullet.png\'); background-attachment: scroll; background-color: transparent; line-height: 1.5; overflow: visible; background-position: 0px 7px; background-repeat: no-repeat no-repeat;\">Have energy and a friendly smile in your voice. Consider standing while speaking to better project your voice.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2 style=\"margin: 1.125em 0px 0.6em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.125; font-family: Oswald, Helvetica, Verdana, Arial, sans-serif; color: #00457c;\">III.   In-Person Interview</h2>\r\n<ul style=\"margin: 0.7em 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; list-style: none; line-height: 1.5;\">\r\n<li style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 10px; border: 0px; background-image: url(\'http://www.project1.com/templates/technik/images/bullet.png\'); background-attachment: scroll; background-color: transparent; line-height: 1.5; overflow: visible; background-position: 0px 7px; background-repeat: no-repeat no-repeat;\">Consider wearing a suit &amp; tie if appropriate or casual business attire. It shows respect and professionalism. (If this is not possible, notify us in advance for guidance.)</li>\r\n<li style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 10px; border: 0px; background-image: url(\'http://www.project1.com/templates/technik/images/bullet.png\'); background-attachment: scroll; background-color: transparent; line-height: 1.5; overflow: visible; background-position: 0px 7px; background-repeat: no-repeat no-repeat;\">Be on time. Leave extra travel time in the event of delays. Plan to arrive 15 minutes before your scheduled time so you can settle down and organize yourself – but do not announce yourself until a couple minutes before the scheduled appointment. If you are running late, make sure you have Project One’s phone # with you so you can alert us in advance and we will notify the client.</li>\r\n<li style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 10px; border: 0px; background-image: url(\'http://www.project1.com/templates/technik/images/bullet.png\'); background-attachment: scroll; background-color: transparent; line-height: 1.5; overflow: visible; background-position: 0px 7px; background-repeat: no-repeat no-repeat;\">Take 4 copies of your resume (as formatted and presented by Project One) in the event you need to share a copy with the client.</li>\r\n<li style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 10px; border: 0px; background-image: url(\'http://www.project1.com/templates/technik/images/bullet.png\'); background-attachment: scroll; background-color: transparent; line-height: 1.5; overflow: visible; background-position: 0px 7px; background-repeat: no-repeat no-repeat;\">Greet the interviewer(s) with a friendly smile and a firm handshake. Show confidence.</li>\r\n<li style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 10px; border: 0px; background-image: url(\'http://www.project1.com/templates/technik/images/bullet.png\'); background-attachment: scroll; background-color: transparent; line-height: 1.5; overflow: visible; background-position: 0px 7px; background-repeat: no-repeat no-repeat;\">Ask the interviewer to describe the position. This will allow you to better target your answers.</li>\r\n<li style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 10px; border: 0px; background-image: url(\'http://www.project1.com/templates/technik/images/bullet.png\'); background-attachment: scroll; background-color: transparent; line-height: 1.5; overflow: visible; background-position: 0px 7px; background-repeat: no-repeat no-repeat;\">Answer the question asked. Be direct and complete, but do not ramble on. Don’t limit your answers to a simple yes or no, but be more descriptive to indicate your knowledge.</li>\r\n<li style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 10px; border: 0px; background-image: url(\'http://www.project1.com/templates/technik/images/bullet.png\'); background-attachment: scroll; background-color: transparent; line-height: 1.5; overflow: visible; background-position: 0px 7px; background-repeat: no-repeat no-repeat;\">Prepare a list of questions to ask beforehand. This shows the client your level of interest and also demonstrates your inquisitiveness and analytical thinking.</li>\r\n<li style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 10px; border: 0px; background-image: url(\'http://www.project1.com/templates/technik/images/bullet.png\'); background-attachment: scroll; background-color: transparent; line-height: 1.5; overflow: visible; background-position: 0px 7px; background-repeat: no-repeat no-repeat;\">Focus on the client’s needs and not your own interests. Think in terms of “what I can do for them,” not “what can they do for me.”</li>\r\n<li style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 10px; border: 0px; background-image: url(\'http://www.project1.com/templates/technik/images/bullet.png\'); background-attachment: scroll; background-color: transparent; line-height: 1.5; overflow: visible; background-position: 0px 7px; background-repeat: no-repeat no-repeat;\">Keep the conversation professional. It’s okay to be friendly, but be careful not to get overly personal.</li>\r\n<li style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 10px; border: 0px; background-image: url(\'http://www.project1.com/templates/technik/images/bullet.png\'); background-attachment: scroll; background-color: transparent; line-height: 1.5; overflow: visible; background-position: 0px 7px; background-repeat: no-repeat no-repeat;\">Never bad mouth a previous client. Always remain professional and limit negative comments. It’s ok to indicate that a previous position was not a good fit.</li>\r\n<li style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 10px; border: 0px; background-image: url(\'http://www.project1.com/templates/technik/images/bullet.png\'); background-attachment: scroll; background-color: transparent; line-height: 1.5; overflow: visible; background-position: 0px 7px; background-repeat: no-repeat no-repeat;\">Never lie or misrepresent your experience since these are grounds for immediate rejection. If you don’t know the answer to a particular question be honest and don’t try to bluff your way through.</li>\r\n<li style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 10px; border: 0px; background-image: url(\'http://www.project1.com/templates/technik/images/bullet.png\'); background-attachment: scroll; background-color: transparent; line-height: 1.5; overflow: visible; background-position: 0px 7px; background-repeat: no-repeat no-repeat;\">For consulting positions, if you are asked about compensation – tell the interviewer that’s a matter they must speak directly with Project One about since the pay rate differs from the bill rate.</li>\r\n<li style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 10px; border: 0px; background-image: url(\'http://www.project1.com/templates/technik/images/bullet.png\'); background-attachment: scroll; background-color: transparent; line-height: 1.5; overflow: visible; background-position: 0px 7px; background-repeat: no-repeat no-repeat;\">For full-time hire positions, if you are asked about compensation – be honest about your salary history and what salary you’re seeking (which should be consistent with what you discussed with Project One.)</li>\r\n<li style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 10px; border: 0px; background-image: url(\'http://www.project1.com/templates/technik/images/bullet.png\'); background-attachment: scroll; background-color: transparent; line-height: 1.5; overflow: visible; background-position: 0px 7px; background-repeat: no-repeat no-repeat;\">Wrap up the interview by summarizing why you would be a good fit. Ask the interviewer if they have any concerns with your experience so you can clarify any misunderstandings. Let them know that you are very interested and want the job.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.7em 0px 1.5em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; line-height: 1.5;\">If you have any further questions or require additional information or assistance, please contact your Project One representative.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>','',1,8,'2013-07-30 05:56:11',575,'','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,0,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','2013-07-30 05:56:11','0000-00-00 00:00:00','{\"image_intro\":\"\",\"float_intro\":\"\",\"image_intro_alt\":\"\",\"image_intro_caption\":\"\",\"image_fulltext\":\"\",\"float_fulltext\":\"\",\"image_fulltext_alt\":\"\",\"image_fulltext_caption\":\"\"}','{\"urla\":false,\"urlatext\":\"\",\"targeta\":\"\",\"urlb\":false,\"urlbtext\":\"\",\"targetb\":\"\",\"urlc\":false,\"urlctext\":\"\",\"targetc\":\"\"}','{\"show_title\":\"\",\"link_titles\":\"\",\